---
import '../styles/design-system.css';

const pageTitle = 'Risk Disclosure | Ramp2Swap';
const pageDescription = 'Risk disclosure for using ramp2swap.com, a DeFi swap platform.';
const lastUpdated = 'March 22, 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/Ramp2Swap.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="page legal-page">
    <div class="ambient-layer" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="ambient-orb ambient-orb--mint-top"></div>
      <div class="ambient-orb ambient-orb--blue-bottom"></div>
      <div class="ambient-orb ambient-orb--mint-center"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content-layer">
      <header class="main-header glass glass-tier-4-nav on-glass" aria-label="Legal page header">
        <div class="brand-nav main-header-nav">
          <a class="brand-row main-header-brand" href="/" aria-label="Ramp2Swap home">
            <img class="logo-horizontal logo-nav-horizontal mobile-nav-horizontal-only main-header-logo" src="/Horizontal_Logo.svg" alt="Ramp2Swap" />
            <img class="logo-mark logo-mark-nav mobile-nav-mark-only" src="/Ramp2Swap.svg" alt="Ramp2Swap mark" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main class="legal-stage">
        <article class="legal-panel card glass glass-tier-2 on-glass">
          <header class="legal-header">
            <p class="ui-label legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
            <h1 class="heading-section">Risk Disclosure</h1>
            <p class="body legal-meta">Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
            <p class="body">
              Digital asset swaps and DeFi interactions involve significant risk. You should carefully evaluate whether
              using Ramp2Swap and any connected protocols is appropriate for your experience level and financial
              circumstances.
            </p>
          </header>

          <section class="legal-section-list">
            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">Market and price risk</h2>
              <p class="body">
                Token prices may change rapidly, spreads may widen, and quoted values may become stale before a
                transaction is executed. You may receive less value than expected or incur a loss.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">Protocol and smart contract risk</h2>
              <p class="body">
                Third-party protocols, bridges, and smart contracts may contain bugs, security vulnerabilities, design
                flaws, governance failures, or other issues that can result in partial or total loss of assets.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">Execution and slippage risk</h2>
              <p class="body">
                Transactions may fail, revert, be delayed, or settle at materially different rates due to slippage,
                congestion, MEV, liquidity fragmentation, oracle issues, or volatile market conditions.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">Wallet and operational risk</h2>
              <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>Loss of private keys, seed phrases, or device control can make assets unrecoverable.</li>
                <li>Approvals or signatures may expose assets to unintended transfers if not reviewed carefully.</li>
                <li>User error, including selecting the wrong token, amount, or chain, can lead to irreversible loss.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">Regulatory and tax risk</h2>
              <p class="body">
                Laws, regulations, sanctions regimes, and tax treatment applicable to digital assets may change quickly
                and differ across jurisdictions. You are responsible for obtaining advice regarding your own compliance
                obligations.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section stack-12">
              <h2 class="heading-card">No guarantee</h2>
              <p class="body">
                Ramp2Swap does not guarantee execution quality, protocol availability, token legitimacy, or suitability
                of any route surfaced through the platform. You should only transact after your own independent review.
              </p>
            </section>
          </section>
        </article>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
